react_usage.answer:
Yes! Each store uses a unique key: ```tsx
const [cart, setCart] = useSlugStore('cart', { items: [] }, { url: true })
const [filters, setFilters] = useSlugStore('filters', { category: 'all' }, { url: true })
```
This creates URLs like `?cart=...&filters=...`

Use the database sync option: ```tsx
const [preferences, setPreferences, { isLoading, error }] = useSlugStore('user-prefs', defaultPrefs, {
  db: { 
    endpoint: '/api/user/preferences',
    method: 'POST'
  }
})

if (isLoading) return <div>Loading preferences...</div>
if (error) return <div>Failed to load: {error.message}</div>

// Updates automatically sync to database
setPreferences({ ...preferences, theme: 'dark' })
```

use_cases.answer:
Perfect use case! Store filters, sorting, and pagination: ```tsx
const [filters, setFilters, { isLoading }] = useSlugStore('product-filters', {
  category: 'all',
  priceRange: [0, 1000],
  sortBy: 'price',
  page: 1
}, { url: true, compress: true })

if (isLoading) return <div>Loading filters...</div>

// Users can bookmark and share filtered results
```

Absolutely! Store widget positions, chart configurations, date ranges: ```tsx
const [dashboard, setDashboard] = useSlugStore('dashboard', {
  widgets: ['sales', 'users', 'revenue'],
  layout: 'grid',
  dateRange: { start: '2025-01-01', end: '2025-12-31' }
}, { url: true, compress: true })

const updateLayout = (newLayout) => {
  setDashboard({ ...dashboard, layout: newLayout })
}
```

Store conversation history and settings: ```tsx
const [chat, setChat] = useSlugStore('ai-chat', {
  messages: [],
  model: 'gpt-4',
  temperature: 0.7,
  systemPrompt: 'You are a helpful assistant'
}, { 
  url: true, 
  compress: true,
  // Note: Consider encryption for sensitive conversations
})
```

Yes! Store canvas elements, zoom, pan, and tool settings: ```tsx
const [canvas, setCanvas] = useSlugStore('canvas', {
  elements: [],
  zoom: 1,
  pan: { x: 0, y: 0 },
  selectedTool: 'rectangle'
}, { url: true, compress: true, debounceMs: 500 })

const addElement = (element) => {
  setCanvas({
    ...canvas,
    elements: [...canvas.elements, element]
  })
}
```

Store todos, filters, and views: ```tsx
const [todos, setTodos] = useSlugStore('todos', {
  items: [],
  filter: 'all', // 'all', 'active', 'completed'
  view: 'list'
}, { url: true, compress: true })

const addTodo = (text) => {
  setTodos({
    ...todos,
    items: [...todos.items, { id: Date.now(), text, done: false }]
  })
}
```
Users can share filtered views or specific todo lists.

frameworks.answer:
Absolutely! The core package is framework-agnostic: ```js
import { encodeState, decodeState } from '@farajabien/slug-store-core'

// Manual URL management
const state = { items: [] }
const slug = await encodeState(state)
window.history.replaceState({}, '', `?state=${slug}`)
```
